Hi Marc,

I'll try to reply to your message as well as I can.

But first of all, I'd like to ask you this: How did you manage to use
the i2c port of your graphics card? Are you using the proprietary
driver of the open source one? I've been trying for moths now, and
haven't been able to do it.

I imagine that you have so many devices because other peripherals you
use are i2c compliant. Or maybe it is just like many devices in linux,
some of them are just there, and not used. I honestly don't have a
better explanation, and anyways, this is not related to ddccontrol.

I have never seen any of the messages that appear in the files you sent.

It seems to me that, because your monitors are not in the database,
they use the very basic VESA configuration, and therefore you lose the
ability to control some of the features of your monitor, but is should
still be usable, at least for brightness and color.
And the output you get from DVI of VGA is definitely different, as the
parameters you can modify are indeed not the same.

To clarify the situation, could you run, for each bus separately, the
ddccontrol -pcd command (the c is important for me). I actually don't
really need the stderr.
Once this is done, could you please send the results back onto the mailing =
list?

I hope that answers some of your questions.

Regards,
Will

